A chieftain of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in Enugu State, Chief Charlie Ugwu has joined the 2023 presidential race, with a call on the PDP stakeholders from the North to concede the presidential ticket to Southern Nigeria, in the interest of equity, inclusiveness, justice, and fairness. Ugwu, a well-known estate developer and PDP chieftain said the socio-economic and political challenges facing the country had become so bad that “no man with capacity, material or intellectual, can watch while this state of affairs ravages our country without doing something”.   Aliko Dangote @ 65     Islamic leader laments poor govt presence in Osogbo     Seek ye first the political kingdom….   Ugwu  pointed out that he had what it takes in terms of intellectual capacity and versatile entrepreneurial skill to steer the Nigerian ship out of the murky waters it found itself at this critical period adding that he decided to throw his hat in the ring for the position in order to salvage the country from the present predicament. “As a consequence of the prevailing situation, I hereby announce my intention to join the presidential race. I have already procured the forms to contest for the presidential ticket under the People’s Democratic Party which has what it takes to take Nigeria to the promised land. He enjoined all members of the party who came from the North to concede the zoning of the presidential ticket to the South so that all will have a sense of belonging since one good turn deserves another.